The addendum is the strength of this article - it tells a really nice story. However, that Description section could be much improved, right down to the level of grammar. Examples that come to mind first: it should be .

And there's plenty of scope for zhooshing it up with more precise, technical language. Saying  would be better tonally. Remember: on this site, you can't be too anal!

The addendum is already pretty great, but there's still room for improvement. (Warning: nitpicky, probably plain-wrong section incoming.) I feel that sprinkling in a few more details about the flames and the navy humanoids would make the reader fear them more. It's a fine line, obviously, because you need to leave some mystery even more. e.g. what if you identify one of the figures as having distinctive red hair, and then establish them as a heroic character with some suitably heroic gesture, and then they're the one who's tragically killed in battle with the Smilodon? That sort of thing.

But on the whole: neat idea, nicely implemented - just work on that Description, please!





